[normal]Misleading ‘hockey sticks’.
[normal]16. 
[normal]The original 
[normal]‘
[normal]hoc
[normal]key 
[normal]stic
[normal]k’ graph of climate change 
[normal]was generated by Professor Michael 
[normal]M
[normal]ann at 
[normal]Pennsylvania State University. The graph figure
[normal]d
[normal] strongly in the IPCC 2000
[normal],
[normal] notably on the cover and 
[normal]five times 
[normal]elsewhere in the report but 
[normal]it 
[normal]is an artifice.  What was not made clear at the time is that the 
[normal]flat part of the graph is a temperature proxy (dendrochronology) whereas the increasing part that was grafted on 
[normal]to it 
[normal]is actual temperature measurements.  
[normal]Tree rings are formed by the activities of the dividing cells of the cambium
[normal],
[normal] a kind of inner sheath
[normal],
[normal]  that generates new phloem to the inside and new xylem to the outside of the cambium.  
[normal]Tree rings are part of the process of plant development in large woody dicotyledonous angiosperms. Because it is development
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]the size of the tree ring is determined by everything that affects 
[normal]all aspects of 
[normal]plant development. Th
[normal]ese are : 
[normal]soil nutrients
[normal] and structure;
[normal] light
[normal] variations;
[normal] 
[normal]carbon dioxide
[normal];
[normal] 
[normal]competition from other trees
[normal];
[normal] disease
[normal];
[normal] predators
[normal];
[normal] 
[normal]age
[normal];
[normal] rainfall
[normal]; previous developmental activity 
[normal]as well as temperature. 
[normal] T
[normal]emperature
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]for which it supposedly acts as a proxy
[normal],
[normal] 
[normal]is just one 
[normal]contributor 
[normal]amongst many
[normal] and of course reflects local conditions only
[normal]. Mann
[normal]’
[normal]s 
[normal]‘H
[normal]ockey 
[normal]S
[normal]tick
[normal]’
[normal] failed to register the historical variation of warm medieval period when Greenland was actually green 
[normal]and 
[normal]the little ice age that dominated 
[normal]in the years 
[normal]1600-1700
[normal]s
[normal]. Greenland was abandoned in the late 1400’s
[normal] as temperatures declined
[normal].
[normal]  
[normal]Tree rings on their
[normal] 
[normal]own are 
[normal]not a
[normal] reliable 
[normal]proxy and examination of tree ring
[normal]s from trees from numerous sites
[normal] indicates inco
[normal]nsistencies. Stable isotope analysis of tree rings may be more useful. 
[normal]Policy 
[normal]was probably influenced by this uncertain information.
[normal]The conflict of carbon dioxide and temperature.
